Fractyl looked decidedly nervous at the prospect of having to go out,
&quot;You actually want me to go with you? After all, I am a scientist, not
a warrior.&quot; Fractyl sounded hopeful at possibly staying behind,
although he knew how often the Megatron of old had tried to push him
to be a warrior.

Iguanus just smiled, &quot;Of course sir.&quot; he said gruffly as he fell in
behind Hydras, his single optic glowing malevolently. His other optic
covered by some sort of patch, mute testimony that unlike Fractyl,
Iguanus was the veteran of a great many battles.

At the door another figure appeared, it was transmetal 2 INFERNO, who
it appears had been guarding the door to Hydras throne room. As Hydras
approached he stepped up, &quot;Sire!&quot; he began as the door slid open, &quot;I
will accompany you as well!&quot;

It would seem that Inferno had gotten over some of his delusion that
Megatron, or in this case Hydras, was his queen, but his devotion to
Hydras was still unswerving and zealous!

